# Tutorial
# To get sounds, item names etc. I added some utility commands to run in game
# Like /flair config                   | to open this config
# /flair log sounds                    | to log all sounds playing around you to a file next to the config
# /flair find <approximate sound name> | to search for similar named sounds
# /flair play <approximate sound name> | to play the first similar named sound
# /flair hand                          | to tell you the item in your hand and copy it to clipboard
# /flair block                         | to tell you the block your looking at and copy it to clipboard

# Item IDs are formatted as follows <namespace:path@meta> so for lapis_lazuli it'd be 'minecraft:dye@4' (yes lapis_lazuli in Minecraft counts as dye number 4, minecraft moment)
# anything from minecraft you don't need to add minecraft:dye you can just do dye
# set item dye@4 play random.pop 1 1

# Each variable has available comparison methods like $DisplayName has [is, isnt, contains, matches]
# Example:
# if item $DisplayName is some_name play dig.wood
# if item $DisplayName isnt some_name play dig.wood
# if item $DisplayName contains some_name play dig.wood
# if item $DisplayName matches some_name play dig.wood

# Available commands:
# volume <volume>
# default <item|craft|drop|typing|inventory> <play sound type>
# allowspam
# if <item|block> <variable> <comparison method> <your input> <play sound type>
# set <item|block> <id> <play sound type>

# <item|block>: whether to check for items or blocks

# All <variable>s:
# For Item: [$DisplayName, $Id, $OreDict, $Damage, $IsBlock]
# For Blocks: [$DisplayName, $Id, $BlockMeta, $HasEntity]

# Different <comparison_method> that <variable> accepts
# $DisplayName = [is, isnt, contains, matches]
# $Id = [is, isnt, contains, matches]
# $OreDict = [is, isnt, contains, matches]
# $Damage = [is, isnt]
# $IsBlock = [is, isnt]
# $BlockMeta = [is, isnt]
# $HasEntity = [is, isnt]

# All <comparison_method>s:
# is | pretty self explanatory
# isnt | also pretty self explanatory
# contains | checks if a word is in a DisplayName, Id etc.
# matches | basically a way more powered `contains`. To learn more it's java flavoured regex, `https://regexlearn.com/` (very powerful)
# Here's an example of how it can match Anything with "Ore" in its name but not match "More" `https://regex101.com/r/vww62m/3`

# All <play sound type>s:
# play <sound> <volume> <pitch>
# playblocksound <break|step> <volume> <pitch>